Percentage difference (PD) allows a relative ranking of the performance of the models during calibration for days to anthesis and maturity, biological and grain yield and LAI maximum variables are presented below for three genotypes i.e.
Lasani−2008=APSIM−Wheat(0.2%)<CERES−Wheat(0.6%)<Nwheat(1.1%)<CROPSIM−Wheat(1.14%);
Punjab−2011=CERES−Wheat(0.3%)<APSIM−Wheat(0.2%)<Nwheat(0.6%)<CROPSIM−Wheat(1.5%);
Galaxy−2013=CROPSIM−Wheat(0%)<APSIM−Wheat(0.4%)<Nwheat(0.6%)<CERES−Wheat(0.7%).
